          What is the job outlook for Software Engineers?

          Powered by Glassdoor Economic Research

          Software engineers mainly work in information technology firms, private technology companies or information technology research. Job prospects for software engineers are very high. There is growth in all provinces with software engineers in high demand in Alberta, Manitoba, Nova Scotia, Ontario, and Prince Edward Island. For those in software engineering, urban areas and cities have the most growth. If you want to be a software engineer, you will need a bachelor’s degree in computer science.

          Frequently Asked Questions

          People who searched for jobs in Canada also searched for .net developer, game programmer, principal engineer, mobile developer, mobile engineer, operations engineer, firmware engineer, qa engineer, devops engineer, jr security analyst. If you're getting few results, try a more general search term. If you're getting irrelevant result, try a more narrow and specific term.
          There are open jobs in several cities in Canada including Toronto, ON, Montreal, QC, Vancouver, BC, Mississauga, ON, Ottawa, ON, Calgary, AB, Waterloo, ON, Edmonton, AB, Kanata, ON, Burnaby, BC

          GEM Health Care

          2.7

          Recreation Programmer

          Yarmouth

          POSITION SCOPE: Assumes responsibility for the daily management, implementation, and evaluation of recreation, volunteer, and pastoral services. Ensures that the program establishes and achieves goals and objectives that are consistent with the mission of the long term care facility.

          Job Duties:

          • Responsible for day-to-day for the preparation, implementation and evaluation of recreation programs that meet a diverse population of residents.
          • Ensures that every resident is involved in identified recreational activities in order to meet the goals of the resident's recreational treatment plan. Leads, instructs, and motivates residents in individual and group leisure pursuits.
          • Setup and organize equipment needed for specific program(s), and oversee residents involved by encouraging participation.
          • Ability to follow safety policy and protocol in the community with residents and volunteers.
          • Effective and professional communication skills with all facility departments.
          • Record and discuss residents' participation levels in programs.
          • Escort, transport, assist residents to and from programs.
          • Other duties as assigned.

          Qualifications and Skills:

          · Post-secondary education required in a related field.

          • Two years of recent related experience or an equivalent combination of education, training and experience (preferred).

          · A Behavioral Therapy Program would be an asset.

          • Excellent communication skills.

          · Must like working with the elderly and creating memorable programs to facilitate with the residents of the home.

          · Must be able to take direction and able to carry out tasks with minimal supervision.

          Certification/Registration/Designation:

          First Aid & CPR.

          Food Handlers Certification.

          Special Knowledge and Skills:

          Experience and knowledge in geriatrics, supervisory experience, excellent communication, organizational, problem solving, interpersonal communication, conflict resolution, time management, and financial management skills.

          #INDLPN

          Job Types: Part-time, Permanent

          Expected hours: 18.75 per week

          Benefits:

          • Extended health care
          • Flexible schedule
          • On-site parking
          • Paid time off
          • RRSP match
          • Vision care

          Flexible language requirement:

          • French not required

          Schedule:

          • 4 hour shift
          • 8 hour shift
          • Day shift
          • Evening shift
          • Weekends as needed

          Ability to commute/relocate:

          • Yarmouth, NS B5A 4J7: reliably commute or plan to relocate before starting work (required)

          Work Location: In person
